ps → backlog clears over time\n\ndef test_game_state_total_cost_empty_players():\n    state = GameState(players={}, ...)\n    assert state.total_cost() == 0.0\n\ndef test_is_round_complete_empty_players():\n    state = GameState(players={}, orders_this_round={}, ...)\n    assert state.is_round_complete() is True  # documents vacuous truth\n\ndef test_create_multiple_games_unique_ids():\n    g1 = engine.create_game(config)\n    g2 = engine.create_game(config)\n    assert g1.game_id != g2.game_id\n```\n\n---\n\n## Priority Map\n\n| Priority | Target | Gap |\n|----------|--------|-----|\n| HIGH | `order_processor.py` direct tests | Covered only via integration |\n| HIGH | `order.py` model tests | Zero tests |\n| HIGH | `process_round` finished-game guard | Untested crash path |\n| HIGH | `demand_pattern=[]` guard | IndexError not caught |\n| MED | Mixed human+AI integration | All-AI only tested |\n| MED | `ai_players/base.py` interface | Abstract class untested |\n| MED | Cost edge cases (float, zero) | Partial |\n| LOW | Backlog clearing multi-round | Gap in dynamics |\n| LOW | `reporting/__init__.py` | Entire module unimplemented |\n\nBiggest risk: `demand_pattern=[]` causes uncaught `IndexError` in `process_round` — document or guard it first.\n",
